The '''1918 Campeonato Nacional'''<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesc/col1819.html RSSSF.com Colombia 1918-1919]</ref> was the first official tournament of the [[Football in Colombia|Colombian football]]. It was only played by two teams from the city of [[Bogotá]]: [[Bartolinos]], a team of the [[Colegio San Bartolomé La Merced|Colegio San Bartolomé]], a state owned school ruled by the [[Jesuits]], and [[Colombia FC]]. This was the only edition held for this competition, being replaced by the [[Categoría Primera A]].

