{{Infobox award |name = James E. Foy, V-ODK Sportsmanship Trophy |image = Foy-ODK Sportsmanship Trophy.jpg |year = 1948 |country = [[United States]] |description = Winning the [[Iron Bowl]] |location = [[Tuscaloosa, Alabama|Tuscaloosa]] or [[Auburn, Alabama|Auburn]], [[Alabama|AL]] |holder = [[Auburn University]] }}
The '''James E. Foy, V-ODK Sportsmanship Trophy''', more commonly known as the Foy-ODK Sportsmanship Trophy, is awarded annually to the winner of the [[Iron Bowl]] football [[List of NCAA college football rivalry games|rivalry]] game between the [[University of Alabama]] and [[Auburn University]].<ref name="ODK1">{{cite web |url=http://www.auburn.edu/odk/Trophy.htm |title=The James E. Foy, V ODK Sportsmanship Trophy |author=ODK Auburn Chapter |publisher=Auburn.edu |accessdate=November 14, 2010}}</ref> The trophy's namesakes are Dean James E. Foy, V, who served at both Auburn and Alabama and the father of photojournalist [[Mary Lou Foy]], and [[Omicron Delta Kappa]] (ODK) National Leadership Honor Society, which has circles at both universities.<ref name="ODK1"/> In years of Auburn victories, the trophy is displayed at the [[Auburn Arena]] in the Jonathan B. Lovelace Hall of Honor, and following Alabama victories, the trophy resides in the [[Paul W. Bryant Museum]].<ref name="ODKTCL">{{cite news |title=After 6-year hiatus, Iron Bowl trophy returns to UA |url=http://www.tuscaloosanews.com/article/20090303/NEWS/903021893/0/ENTERTAINMENT |first=Adam |last=Jones |newspaper=The Tuscaloosa News |date=March 3, 2009 |accessdate=November 14, 2010}}</ref>
The trophy was established in 1948 by the two circles of Omicron Delta Kappa to signify a good relationship between the two schools despite the bitter rivalry.<ref name="ODK1"/><ref name="ODKTCL"/> In 1978, upon his retirement from Auburn University, the trophy was dedicated to Dean James Foy because of his importance to both schools.<ref name="ODK1"/><ref name="ODKBHM">{{cite news |title=James Edgar Foy, beloved Auburn dean, dies at 93 |url=http://blog.al.com/spotnews/2010/10/james_edgar_foy_beloved_auburn.html |agency=Associated Press |publisher=al.com |date=October 10, 2010 |accessdate=November 14, 2010}}</ref> Foy graduated from the University of Alabama and served there as the Assistant Dean of Students before serving as Dean of Students at Auburn University. Foy also served as the Faculty Secretary, the key faculty officer for ODK, for both circles.
Each year, the trophy is presented to the winning school by the losing school at the winners' home basketball game in the [[Iron Bowl of Basketball]], and then resides at the winning university through the following year.<ref name="ODKTCL"/> The ODK president from the losing school presents the trophy to the ODK president of the winning school during halftime of the basketball game, and tradition dictates that the presenter also sing the fight song of the winning school. This tradition is seen at University of Alabama SGA as President James Fowler sings the Auburn fight song in 2011.<ref name="ODKTCL"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bavYYAMXRxg|title=Auburn presented Iron Bowl trophy, fight song sung|first=|last=Michael Casagrande|date=22 January 2011|publisher=|accessdate=13 April 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref> The circle from the losing school also treats the circle from winning school to dinner.<ref name="ODK1"/>
