{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Napps | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Wrotham]], [[Kent]] | coordinates = {{coord|51.308|N|0.309|E|type:landmark|display=title, inline}} (approx) | establishment = | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1815 | club1 = Kent | date = 25 February | year = 2012 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/860.html CricketArchive }}
'''Napps''' was a [[cricket]] ground at [[Wrotham]] in [[Kent]]. One match played on the ground was given retrospective [[first-class cricket]] status. This took place in 1815, when [[Kent county cricket teams|a Kent side]] played host to an [[Non-international England cricket teams|England XI]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/860_f.html First-Class Matches played on Napps, Wrotham], CricketArchive. Retrieved 2017-12-17.</ref> The only other recorded match at this venue was played the following year between a Kent XI and Wrotham.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/860_misc.html Other matches played on Napps, Wrotham], CricketArchive. Retrieved 2017-12-17.</ref>
