{{Infobox sport governing body | assocname = Orienteering Australia | abbrev = | logo = Orienteering Australia.JPG | sport = [[Orienteering]] | category = | image = | caption = | jurisdiction = [[Australia]] | founded = | aff = [[International Orienteering Federation|IOF]] | affdate = | region = Oceania | regionyear = | headquarters = | location = | president = Blair Trewin | chairman = | chairperson = | chair = | chiefexec = | secretary = | coach = | womenscoach = | key staff = | operating income = | sponsor = | year closed = | replaced = | prevfounded = | url = www.orienteering.asn.au | countryflag = Australia | countryflag2 = | countryflag3 = }}
'''Orienteering Australia''' is the National organisation responsible for the governing, organisation and promotion of [[orienteering]] in [[Australia]]. It is a Full Member of the [[International Orienteering Federation]].<ref>http://www.orienteering.org/i3/index.php?/iof2006/iof/member_federations/iof_member_federations#AUS {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080618185711/http://www.orienteering.org/i3/index.php?%2Fiof2006%2Fiof%2Fmember_federations%2Fiof_member_federations |date=2008-06-18 }} Retrieved on 20th of June 2008</ref> Orienteering Australia has its own publication ''The Australian Orienteer''.<ref>http://orienteering.asn.au/australianorienteer Retrieved on 20th of June 2008</ref>
== Governance == The Council which governs Orienteering Australia is made up of representatives from each association. Daily business is handled by an elected Board of 6-8 directors. Committees and ''Officers'' offer specialist advice to both the Council and Board.<ref name="aboutoa">{{cite web |url=http://www.orienteering.asn.au/administration/ |title=About Orienteering Australia |publisher=orienteering.asn.au |accessdate=12 January 2009}}</ref>
== Finance == The Board Director of Finance is Bruce Bowen.<ref name="board">{{cite web |url=http://www.orienteering.asn.au/administration/board/ |title=Orienteering Australia Board 2008 |accessdate=12 January 2009}}</ref> Orienteering Australia is sponsored principally by the [[Australian Sports Commission]].<ref>http://www.orienteering.asn.au/home/ Retrieved on 20th of June 2008</ref> Some sponsorship is also gained from [[Silva]], which specifically sponsors the National Orienteering League. Additional sponsorship is received from the Melbourne Bicycle Centre.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orienteering.asn.au/sponsors/ |title=Sponsorship |publisher=orienteering.asn.au |accessdate=12 January 2009}}</ref>
== Members of the federation == '''Orienteering Australia''' is a federation made up of the 7 associations, with each State or territory of the commonwealth having a federation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orienteering.asn.au/state-organisations/ |title=Federation Members |accessdate=24 September 2014}}</ref>
== History == Orienteering Australia was founded in 1970, and joined the [[International Orienteering Federation]] the same year.<ref name="Vamplew Australian Society for Sports History 1994 p. 325">{{cite book |last=Vamplew |first=W. |author2=Australian Society for Sports History |title=The Oxford Companion to Australian Sport |publisher=Oxford University Press |series=Oxford Companions Series |year=1994 |isbn=978-0-19-553568-6 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WotYAAAAYAAJ |access-date=17 November 2018 |page=325}}</ref> Australia participated in the [[World Orienteering Championships]] first time in 1972.<ref name="o1987">{{cite book |title=Orienteringsidretten i Norge gjennom 90 år |editor=Knut Berglia |editor2=Tom-Erik Brohaug |editor3=Kristoffer Staver |editor4=Kaare Thuesen |editor5=Torgeir Strandhagen |language=Norwegian |year=1987 |publisher=[[Norges Orienteringsforbund]] |page=278}}</ref> The 1985 World Championships were held in [[Bendigo]], Australia.<ref>Berglia 1987, pp. 216–217</ref>
Individual world champion from Australia is [[Johanna Allston]], who won a gold medal in sprint in 2006. She also won the middle distance in the [[Orienteering at the World Games|World Games]] in 2009.
