{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}} {{Use British English|date=March 2016}} {{Infobox cricketer | name = Read | image = | country = England | fullname = unknown | nickname = | birth_date = c.1740 | birth_place = [[England]] | batting = unknown hand | bowling = underarm: unknown hand and type | role = batsman | club1 = unknown | year1 = c.1761–1775 | club2 = | year2 = | date = 19 March | year = 2013 | columns = 0 | source = [[Arthur Haygarth]] }}
'''Read''' (first name and dates unknown) was an English [[first-class cricket|first-class]] [[cricket]]er who made a single appearance for [[All-England cricket teams|All-England]] against the [[Hambledon Club]] at the [[Artillery Ground]] in 1773.<ref name="CA9">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/0/9.html |publisher=''CricketArchive'' |title=Kent v Surrey 1773 |accessdate=19 March 2013}}</ref> Blake made one known first-class appearance, scoring 13 runs in his only innings. He did not bowl.<ref name="CA9"/><ref>Haygarth, p.7.</ref>
As Read had established his reputation by 1773, he must have been active for some years previously and his career probably began in the 1760s. Very few players were mentioned by name in contemporary reports and there are no other references to Read.
