{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = St George's Cricket Ground | nickname = The Dragons | country = England | image = St.Georges Cricket Club aerial.jpg | caption = Aerial view of St.Georges Cricket Club in 1985 | location = [[Telford]], [[Shropshire]] | establishment = 1922 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1957-1958 & 1967-2001 | club1 = [[Shropshire County Cricket Club|Shropshire]] | date = 15 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/785.html Ground profile }}
'''St George's Cricket Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Telford]], [[Shropshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1957, when [[Shropshire County Cricket Club|Shropshire]] played the [[Derbyshire County Cricket Club|Derbyshire Second XI]] in the grounds first [[Minor Counties Championship]] match. From 1957 to present, the ground has hosted 20 Minor Counties Championship matches<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/785_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on St George's Cricket Ground]</ref> and 3 [[MCCA Knockout Trophy]] matches.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/785_mint.html MCCA Knockout Trophy Matches played on St George's Cricket Ground]</ref>
The ground has also held [[List-A cricket|List-A]] matches. The first List-A match Shropshire play a [[Yorkshire County Cricket Club|Yorkshire]] side that contained the likes of [[Geoffrey Boycott]] in the [[1984 NatWest Trophy]]; a match Shropshire famously won by 37 runs.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/44/44933.html Shropshire v Yorkshire, National Westminster Bank Trophy 1984 (1st Round)]</ref> From 1984 to 2000, the ground held 7 List-A matches, the last of which saw Shropshire play [[Somerset County Cricket Club|Somerset]] in the [[2000 NatWest Trophy]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/785_a.html List-A Matches played on St George's Cricket Ground]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, St George's Cricket Ground is the home ground of [http://www.stgeorgescc.org.uk St.Georges Cricket Club], founded in 1922, whose forerunner was St.Georges Bible Class C.C. Today, St.Georges fields four Saturday sides and has a junior section which accepts children from school year 2. <ref>[http://www.stgeorgescc.org.uk/ St George's Cricket Club]</ref>
