{{Infobox settlement <!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions --> | name = Staouéli | official_name = Commune of Staouéli | native_name = سطوالي | native_name_lang = ar<!-- ISO 639-2 code e.g. "fr" for French.--> | type = [[Municipalities of Algeria|Municipality]] | image_skyline = Sidi fredj complexe.jpg | image_alt = | image_caption = Sidi Fredj resort | image_shield = | nickname = | pushpin_map = Algeria | pushpin_map_alt = | pushpin_map_caption = Location of Staouéli within Algeria | coordinates = {{coord|36|45|N|2|53|E|region:DZ-16_type:adm3rd|display=inline,title}} | coor_pinpoint = | coordinates_footnotes = | subdivision_type = [[List of sovereign states|Country]] | subdivision_name = {{flag|Algeria}} | subdivision_type1 = [[Provinces of Algeria|Province]] | subdivision_name1 = [[Algiers Province|Algiers]] | subdivision_type2 = [[Districts of Algeria|District]] | subdivision_name2 = [[Zéralda District|Zéralda]] | established_title = <!-- Founded --> | established_date = | seat_type = [[Capital (political)|District&nbsp;seat]] | seat = | government_footnotes = | leader_title = [[People's Municipal Assembly|PMA Seats]] | leader_name = 11 | leader_title1 = PMA&nbsp;president | leader_name1 = Saïd Bouifer(2002-2007) | leader_title2 = <!-- District&nbsp;chief --> | leader_name2 = | unit_pref = Metric<!-- or US or UK --> | area_footnotes = | area_total_km2 = 22.23 | elevation_footnotes = | elevation_m = | population_footnotes = | population_total = 38915 | population_as_of = 1998 | population_density_km2 = auto | population_demonym = | timezone1 = [[Central European Time|CET]] | utc_offset1 = +01 | postal_code_type = [[List of postal codes in Algeria|Postal code]] | postal_code = 16101 | area_code_type = <!-- [[Area Code]] --> | area_code = <!-- +213 (0) --> | blank_name_sec1 = [[Office of National Statistics (Algeria)|ONS]] code | blank_info_sec1 = 1645 | website = <!-- [http://www.example.com example.com] --> | footnotes = }}
'''Staouéli''' is a [[municipalities of Algeria|municipality]] in [[Algiers Province|Algiers]] [[provinces of Algeria|province]], [[Algeria]]. It is located in [[Zéralda District|Zéralda]] [[districts of Algeria|district]], on a [[Presque-isle]] on the [[Mediterranean Sea]], hosting the [[resort town]] of [[Sidi Fredj]]. There was a [[Grand Prix motor racing|Grand Prix]] circuit located in Staouéli. Grands Prix were held there from 1928–1930, but the circuit is no longer operational.<ref>{{cite web|last=Galpin|first=Darren|title=Staouéli|url=http://www.silhouet.com/motorsport/tracks/africa/staoueli.html|work=GEL Motorsport Information Page|accessdate=24 April 2013}}</ref>
In 1843 the [[Trappists]] obtained a grant of 2500 acres of land on the site of the [[Battle of Staouéli]] (fought on June 19, 1830 during the [[French conquest of Algeria]]). Here they have built a monastery where some 100 monks lived and worked. On the wall of the monastery is the inscription: ''S'il est triste de vivre à la Trappe, qu'il est doux d'y mourir'' (While it is sad to live here, it is sweet to die here).
==See also== [[Battle of Staouéli]]
